SIMPLE: hissing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hissing
<hw>Hiss"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of emitting a
hiss or hisses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The occasion of contempt; the object of scorn and
derision.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will make this city desolate, and a <qex>hissing</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Jer. xix. 8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hissingly</ent>⟦br⟧
